	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Monday&#44; 2 of Kislev&#40;November&#41; 1865</date>.</p>
				<p>Greetings to my friend&#44; my dear&#44; the wise&#44; the accomplished&#44; who seeks<lb/> the welfare of his people&#44; <persName>Eliezar Lippman Leeser</persName>&#44; Dear friend&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Only yesterday&#44; the house was filled with light to see your<lb/> bright and shining words. <persName>Mr. von Beil</persName><add>&#63;</add> was to see me only yesterday&#44;<lb/> and is now pressing for a decision&#44; but this is very hard to make. This<lb/> matter is terribly involved. There are 50 kinds of things against it<lb/> and a like number in favor. He can and may not invalidate himself from<lb/> being a <persName>Cohen</persName>. First of all&#44; we must seek &#8212; I say seek &#8212; I want to use the<lb/> definite term&#44; for I am among those who are fearful for the teaching of<lb/> tradition &#8212; not to express anything that will make her valid as a Jewess.<lb/> This is what you have failed to do&#44; to make the mother a Jewess. If she<lb/> is a Jewess&#44; then the thing could be done&#44; for then the Biblical law no<lb/> longer applies&#45; that the children are of a Jewish father and they can be<lb/> full Jews. It will be difficult. Let her go to the ritual bath only<lb/> because of a doubt of Jewishness. Above all comes the question&#44; whether<lb/> it is possible that the mother&#44; who lacks only the ritual bath&#44; does this<lb/> only because&#44; as <persName>von Beil</persName> says&#44; she is a cripple. Perhaps it could be<lb/> done by force. <sic>write</sic> to me about it. This would be the first step&#44; then<lb/> we shall see what is to be done further. I am still not clear about it&#44;<lb/> and should like to have the whole matter thoroughly explained&#44; in order&#44;<lb/> if possible&#44; to turn it into a <hi rend="underline">fait accompli</hi>. For the moment&#44; I am too<lb/> much worried with the pains of editorship. <persName>Isaacs</persName> is silent <del>after</del> ever since I had<lb/> myself <del>set him aside</del> refuted him&#44; well but quietly. He and his are mean fellows.<lb/> The free school here is humbug&#44; Its matzo&#45;baking president is the lowest<lb/> of the low &#8212; of the vice&#45;president. One of the chief teachers&#44; also a<lb/> &#8212; did some unclean things with children in other schools. Should one<lb/> keep quiet about such things&#63; That is why I have written that one who<lb/> uncovers only one portion merely covers up double the amount. I don&#39;t<lb/> want to speak about other things.. Keep for me the reports of the assembly</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">2</p>
				<p>of delegates&#44; also advertisements.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With the help of God I shall begin this week to print&#44; with<lb/> your permission&#44; your translation of my introduction to <hi rend="underline"><persName>Esther</persName></hi> &#8212;&#8212; .<lb/> You may also remove certain things from the &#8212;&#8212;as&#44; for example&#44; that<lb/> congregations ought to make clear to themselves their own principles&#44;<lb/> and that religious leaders should give an honest and thorough report of<lb/> their trust.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Writing with broken &#8212; and expecting your answer&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Your friend&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName></p>
		</body>
